  <div class="mt-12 section">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-light tracking-tight sm:text-3xl text-fg">Sayan Mohsin</h1>
    <div class="mt-2 h-[1px] w-12 bg-signal" style="box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(255,107,0,0.4)"></div>
    <p class="mt-3 text-dim/60 mono text-xs">Toronto, Canada</p>
    <p class="mt-1 text-dim">Senior Software Engineer @ Intellistack</p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-4 text-dim leading-relaxed border-l border-line pl-5 section">
    <p>
      I write code that writes code. Sometimes it works on the first try. Usually it doesn't.
      That's what makes it fun.
    </p>
    <p>
      I design and build distributed systems across the stack — real-time data pipelines,
      AI agents that code and review, infrastructure that stays up. I focus on clean
      architecture and pragmatic system design, shipping products that are reliable
      end-to-end without the over-engineering tax.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 section">
    <h2 class="mono text-xs text-dim/50 tracking-[0.1em] uppercase mb-6">What I Build</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div class="border-l border-line pl-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm text-fg">Distributed systems</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-dim leading-relaxed">
          Real-time data pipelines, event-driven architectures, and infrastructure
          that doesn't fall over at 3am. Kafka, Temporal, and the kind of systems
          where you actually need a consistent hash ring.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l border-line pl-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm text-fg">AI agents</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-dim leading-relaxed">
          Agents that write code, review PRs, and deploy themselves — then
          explain what they did so you don't wake up to a page at midnight.
          MCP protocols, tool-use, and the messy reality of making AI
          reliable in production.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l border-line pl-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm text-fg">Clean architecture</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-dim leading-relaxed">
          Systems that are easy to change, cheap to operate, and boring in the
          best way. I've learned that the right abstraction today is worth ten
          rewrites tomorrow — and that most abstractions aren't the right one.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l border-line pl-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm text-fg">Open source</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-dim leading-relaxed">
          I build tools I wish existed — a clipboard manager that respects privacy
          (clipbuf), a data engine for AI agents (thingd), and whatever else
          scratches an itch. Open source isn't charity, it's how I think out loud.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 section">
    <h2 class="mono text-xs text-dim/50 tracking-[0.1em] uppercase mb-4">What I Believe</h2>
    <div class="border-l-2 pl-5 py-3 space-y-2" style="border-color: #ff6b00; box-shadow: -2px 0 12px rgba(255,107,0,0.08)">
      <p class="text-sm text-dim leading-relaxed">
        <span class="text-fg font-medium" style="text-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(255,107,0,0.2)">Build it right. Scale it well.</span>
        — these aren't opposites. They're the same thing when you don't cut corners.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-sm text-dim">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-signal mono text-xs">&rarr;</span>
          <span>Don't build layers nobody understands</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-signal mono text-xs">&rarr;</span>
          <span>Don't optimize before you know what's slow</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-signal mono text-xs">&rarr;</span>
          <span>Don't ignore how it actually runs</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-signal mono text-xs">&rarr;</span>
          <span>Don't skip the docs — future you will forget</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

